anvil (1.2.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Added project template generator with -c flag
  * Interactive project creation with customizable structure
  * Support for src and include folder options
  * Single and multi-target project templates
  * Automatic hello world program generation with VERSION macro
  * Smart project naming (current directory or custom name)

 -- Dexter <dexter@example.com>  Thu, 23 Oct 2025

anvil (1.1.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Added built-in auto-updater functionality
  * New -u flag to update to latest version
  * Support for updating to specific versions with -u <version>
  * GitHub API integration for release management
  * Automatic .deb package download and installation
  * CLI with update commands

 -- Dexter <dexter@example.com>  Thu, 23 Oct 2025

anvil (1.1.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Added version support in build.conf files
  * Automatic VERSION macro definition for C code
  * Version information in generated Makefiles
  * Enhanced configuration parser for version field
  * Updated examples with version usage

 -- Dexter <dexter@example.com>  Thu, 23 Oct 2025 

anvil (1.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fixed multi-target watch mode support
  * Fixed string trimming bug causing spaces in variable names
  * Improved watch system to monitor all target sources
  * Added CMake build configuration options
  * Enhanced multi-target Makefile generation

 -- Dexter <dexter@example.com>  Mon, 21 Oct 2025 

anvil (1.0.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release of Anvil build system
  * Simple configuration file syntax for C projects
  * Automatic source file discovery with glob patterns
  * Watch mode for automatic rebuilds on file changes
  * Watch & Run mode for automatic rebuild and execution
  * Colored terminal output for better user experience
  * Cross-platform support (Linux, Windows, macOS)
  * Human-readable code comments throughout codebase

 -- Dexter <dexter@example.com>  Sun, 19 Oct 2025 